                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think we can all agree that Persistant casting in it's actual form seems a waste of AA...
<br />
Like it was pointed for persistant casting to go off the following has to take place:
<br />
-You must be casting a spell
<br />
-You must be stunned during the casting of that spell
<br />
-Then you have on "RARE OCCURANCE" a chance that persistant casting will go off...
<br />
-Even if it goes off, it does not guarantee you that your spell will be channelled since when you're stunned you get pushed a lot.
<br />

<br />
considering all of this, it explains why i saw persistant casting go off twice only since i purchased this AA (at lvl 3 right when god went out).
<br />

<br />
However, i feel something should be done to improve it a bit:
<br />

<br />
-Allow for a persistant casting check when we BEGIN to cast. Now it does not seem overpowered for me... 
<br />
-Maybe improve the % of chances that persistant casting could go of?
<br />
